.TH GAT-SESSIONS 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-sessions \- list live gat tmux sessions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat sessions
.RB [ \-\-format
.IR text|json ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Enumerates tmux sessions whose names start with
.I gat\-
and reports each one's attach state, window count, branch, path, and
description, read from the
.I @gat_*
options gat sets when it creates a session. Sessions created outside gat are not
listed. When no tmux server is running, prints a friendly message and exits
successfully. Requires
.BR tmux (1)
on
.IR PATH .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-format " text|json"
Output format.
.SH "OUTPUT COLUMNS (TEXT)"
.IR Session ", " A " (attached marker), " Win " (window count), " Branch ", and " "Description / Path" .
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat sessions
gat sessions \-\-json | jq '.[] | select(.attached)'
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-switch (1),
.BR gat\-tmux (1)
